# GitHub deploy — Dr. Melani

## Repository

- **Project root:** `/Users/melanishrestha/melani_assistant`
- **Remote:** `https://github.com/melanikshrestha-boop/dr.-Melani.git`
- **Default branch:** `main`

When the user asks to deploy, push, sync, or publish to GitHub, work from the project root above.

## Never commit

Personal data and secrets live outside the repo in `~/.melani_assistant/`. Never add or push:

- `config.json`, `content_config.json`, `phone_url.json`, `content_phone_url.json`
- `health.db`, `content.db`, OAuth tokens, tunnel logs/PIDs, API keys, passphrases, PIN overrides
- Anything under `~/.melani_assistant/health_data/`, `content_data/`, or `content_inbox/`

Ensure `.gitignore` exists and includes at least:

```
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.DS_Store
.env
*.log
*.pid
```

## First-time setup

If there is no `.git` directory:

1. `git init`
2. Add `.gitignore` if missing
3. `git remote add origin https://github.com/melanikshrestha-boop/dr.-Melani.git`
4. Stage source only (skip duplicate `* copy*` backup files unless the user wants them)
5. Create the initial commit **only when the user asks**
6. `git branch -M main` then `git push -u origin main`

## Ongoing deploy

1. `git status`, `git diff`, and `git log -3` to understand changes
2. Commit **only when the user explicitly asks** — never auto-commit after feature work
3. Push: `git push origin main` (or the current branch)
4. If push is rejected, pull/rebase first; never force-push `main` unless the user explicitly requests it

## Auth

Prefer `gh` when installed. Otherwise use `git push` over HTTPS or SSH. If auth fails, tell the user to sign in (`gh auth login` or configure a GitHub credential/SSH key) and retry.

## After push

Confirm the remote URL and branch pushed. Remind the user that runtime data stays local in `~/.melani_assistant/` and is not backed up by this repo.
